      <h2>Are We COPing?</h2>
      <h4>Transforming Artistic Engagement Around COP26 and Beyond.</h4>
      <p>Dates: <b class='names'>8 September 2020</b></p>
      <p>Time: <b class='names'>7:00 pm GMT</b></p>
      <p>Location: <b class='names'>Zoom</b>
      </p>
      <details>
        <summary>We are delighted to announce this digital workshop generously supported by
          Creative Carbon Scotland. Created by Matteo Menapace, a game designer formerly
          in residence at the V&amp;A, it will provide a structured format for creative practitioners,
          researchers and policymakers to discuss urgent challenges ahead of the UN Climate
          Change Conference (COP26) due to take place in Glasgow in November 2021.</summary>
        <p>Set up as a role-playing game, this workshop will enable participants to step out of
          their daily roles and imagine solutions to shared problems. After all, play, as once
          noted by cultural historian Huizinga, is &#39;older than culture.&#39;</p>
        <p>Further details can be found <a
            href='https://www.creativecarbonscotland.com/event/green-tease-are-we-coping/' target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.</p>
      </details>
